      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SAINT CRUSADER (5) looks close to a win having placed the last two times he raced here, leading and fighting well to go under by a head as runner-up last start. Draws wider but could break through if things go his way. COOL NIGHT (8) made a good return to the Harmey stable when he finished third at his latest appearance at this venue, racing parked but boxing on to be beaten 5.4 metres. May need a bit of luck negotiating a very wide starting position but with even luck he is good enough to take out a race like this. ROCKTAGONAL (3) had this same draw when he beat SAINT CRUSADER for a last-start win by a head at this circuit. Must be respected along with GROSSO NASO (7) who found form with a last-start win at Tamworth.",
